description:
This bright comfortable one bedroom apartment with a architectural thouch has a true cosy feeling! It comfortably fits two and is centrally located on a quiet street, near everything you need! Shops, musea, transport, dining, bars and supermarket!
Take a look at the floorplan to save money.

The space
This 60m² apartment is uniquely located around the corner of Rotterdam's famous cultural street 'Witte de Withstraat' with restaurants, arts and little shops. It's a 5 min. walk to the shopping center, the musea, the park and a 5 min. walk to the river Maas. There is a small supermarket around the corner.
The apartment is nicely renewed in 2021. There is a balcony on the street side and one on the back side. The apartment is nicely furnished and has a warm cosy appeal. Wifi available (the most comprehensive internet package).
max 2 persons.
Non smoking

Checking in and out can be flexible, it depends on if there are new guests arriving

description:
The space
Welcome to Rotterdam!

This appartment is excellently located on the Mathensserlaan in the city center. Within 10 minutes walking distance you can find the musea park, the Erasmus University and Rotterdam Central Station. The shopping center is located around the corner and many pubs and restaurants are present in this area too.

The apparmtent is fully equiped for long and short stay included Free WIFI. The appartment suits 2 persons. There is a living room with a fireplace, a kitchen,a conservatory, a bedroom and a small bathroom. The appartment is on the second floor so please note that you have to walk up 2 steep stairs. Have a look at the pictures if you would like to see more.

The total space is 90 square meters. It's possible to have breakfast (for extra charge) in the hotel next to the appartment. There is also a private car park available (for extra charge). The rental price includes cleaning 1 time per week!

The apartment has a nice entrance hall with space for bicycles. description:
Enjoy Rotterdam the Rotterdam way. On a classic Amsterdam ferry (1911) in a comfortable apartment with sunny deck terrace, a view on the New Meuse and the Rotterdam skyline. Sleep tightly in the bow of the ship on the rhythm of the tide.

The space
Loftboat Rotterdam Kralingen is a former Amsterdam IJ-ferry dating from 1911. The boat was converted into a comfortable 55 m2 guest apartment (1-5 persons). There is a large, sunny private deck terrace with a view on the New Meuse and the Rotterdam skyline. The apartment has its own entrance and offers a great deal of privacy.

The salon is flooded with natural light. The kitchen is ready for cooking, and coffee and tea are present. The apartment has a work space, a wood-burning stove, TV, tuner/amplifier, CD/DVD player, an IPod connection and WiFi. All rooms have central heating.

There is bathroom with shower, a separate bedroom with a double bed and sleeping options for 3 in the salon.

description:
This comfortable apartment is fully self catered and on an amazing ship that lies in the centre of Rotterdam. In walking distance of the Markthal, Coolsingel, Koopgoot and Erasmusbrug. Enjoy everything that Rotterdam has to offer. Look for me on Social Media use @ HouseboatRotterdam. I share tips and nice pictures there.

The space
This Ship, a Spits, was build in 1937. It was used to carry goods over the Dutch rivers. In 2009 the biggest part of the Ship, the cargo hold, was fully renovated and made into accommodation for guests to stay in. This means that the space is clean and comfortable, and at the same time you still feel that you're on a ship. Rotterdam, being an seaport, is connected to the sea. This means that the ship moves with the tides. The difference is 2 meters, so it's possible you go into town and have to climb the walkway while leaving the ship and when you come back you have to climb the walkway again while entering the ship.

description:
Heerlijke en rustige zeer ruime kamer met eigen bad, douche en toilet. Je hebt toegang tot een gezamenlijke en gedeelde woonkamer en aangrenzende keuken met een fantastisch uitzicht over de authentieke haven. Kamer is in een heel oud monumentaal pand. Met oneffenheden die horen bij een oud huis. Laat je verrassen door een prachtig origineel authentiek middel eeuws plafond. Vanuit dit pand is het centrum op 10 minuten loopafstand, metro en tram om de hoek.

The space
De kamer is in een heerlijk licht huis..met heel veel ruimte! De kamer heeft een plafond uit 1790, die geschilderd is door reizende schilders. Uniek en je zult deze ervaring nergens anders krijgen!

Other things to note
Wanneer je op zoek bent naar een steriele en/of strak design studio is deze kamer niet geschikt. Kun je echter genieten van een oud huis uit 1594 met bijbehorende oneffenheden dan is deze kamer geweldig!

description:
Spending the night at this sustainable campsite is a guarantee for the most special night's sleep you've ever had. You'll sleep in one of the various small-scale architectural objects between fragrant plants in less than ten minutes from the city centre of Rotterdam and a stone's throw from the river the Maas. The sleeping objects are smaller than a tiny house, more exciting than a tent and different from all glamping accommodations. On the campsite are sanitary facilities and a common room.

The space
“Do you always know what you see?” You will initially see a normal brick wall, our brain fills in the missing pieces. However, as you get closer, no stone seems to touch the other. Every stone floats in the air, but together they form a solid brick wall. Floating Bricks combines two residual flows; glass plates and rejected brick slips. Designed by ROFFAA architects.

You can also check out our other objects at culturecampsite.com

Guest acces

description:
Penthouse Prison, located in the heart of Rotterdam situated on the top floor of the former PoliceBuilding.
A UNIQUE EXPERIENCE FOR FRIENDS AND FAMILY

Penthouse Prison is part of a social project, called Heilige Boontjes. The basic idea is that young Rotterdammers - that have a so-called distance to the labour market - will be helped and trained to get and hold a job in the cafe, restaurant on the ground floor and the Bed&Breakfast on the top floor.

The space
Of the complex of 6 prison cells, 4 cells have been converted with modern beds for comfort, but the general impression of the prison is still intact. There is one cell with a queen sized bed and three with a single bed. One cell is used as a toilet and one is used for general purpose to relax with a tv and books.
Thanks to the unwavering commitment of Daan Bakker from Daf-architecten, the building has been given a new future while retaining its social purpose.

description:
Een verblijf op een van onze Wikkelboats in de Rijnhaven is zeker onvergetelijk! Op een toplocatie, gelegen tussen de metropolische Kop van Zuid en het hippe Katendrecht en vlakbij het bruisende centrum. Wikkelboats zijn zeer comfortabele tiny houseboats welke multifunctioneel en duurzaam zijn ingericht. Kom heerlijk tot rust, hangend in de tweepersoons hangmat onder de veranda en/of geniet van het prachtige uitzicht om je heen vanaf je ruime terras aan het water...wedden dat je betoverd wordt?

The space
Je hebt twee fijne woon-/slaapkamers, een badkamer, keukentje en een fijn terras met hangmat en ook nog een buitendouche.
Ter info: tussen ~10.30-15.00u kan terrasluik naar kelder op voorterras door ons (schoonmaakteam) worden gebruikt voor ophalen en opbergen van spullen. Uiteraard proberen we jullie daarbij zo min mogelijk te storen!

description:
The Cuckoo Clock is a powerful expression of some of the artist’s personal passions. Yes, this is a pretty sizable rendition of a classic cuckoo clock. However, the trademark Coenen details probably have little to do with the traditional timepiece he once bought in the Czech Republic, which inspired the work.

The space
Instead we see Marshall amplifiers and massive heavy metal guitars: a tribute to the maker’s favorite band Slayer. Never eager to please society’s esthetic common denominator, Coenen added plenty of skulls and two giant Viking swords to set the mood.

We encourage guests sleeping in the Cuckoo Clock to go a little cuckoo themselves and occasionally announce time in whatever way they please.

description:
Welcome to the Candy House, where one classic story is transformed into a two-story building full of colorful delight. Over the top decorations in ceramic and sculptured wood lure in whoever gets lost in the urban forest that is Rotterdam. This room represents all the sweet temptations a modern day hedonists may desire. From cookie windows and chocolate stucco, to more adult treats such as ‘rave sweets’ and liquor bottles.

The space
It’s Hansel and Gretel on steroids, a chemical fairytale, or an average weekend for Dutch youngsters if you buy into stereotypes about our country some like to advertise. One thing is certain, no other hotel in the world has a room like this.

description:
Fijne houten vrijstaand chalet met ruime tuin dichtbij het Oostvoornse Meer. Het gezellige dorpscentrum van Oostvoorne bevindt zich op 20 minuten loopafstand en heeft supermarkten, diverse winkels en leuke restaurants met terrasjes. Er gaan van daaruit bussen naar verschillende plaatsen in de omgeving.

Het chalet staat op het gezinsvriendelijke vakantiepark Molecaten Kruiningergors met buitenzwembad, speeltuin, strandje, snackbar, winkeltje en in de zomervakantie activiteiten voor kinderen.

The space
Er is 1 ruime slaapkamer met tweepersoons bed + een tweepersoons slaapbank in de woonkamer. Het chalet heeft een eigen badkamer met douche en toilet en een volledige keuken met 4-pits gaskookplaat, magnetron, koelkast met vriesvak, waterkoker en Senseo koffiezetapparaat.

Other things to note
Er is (tegen betaling) wifi verkrijgbaar via het park.

description:
A cosy family house in Barendrecht, close to the big city Rotterdam and the River the 'Oude maas'. The house is a typical Dutch home, attached to other houses in a quiet and cosy neighbourhood. The house is very spacious with a front and back garden.

The space
When you enter the house on the ground floor you will find a spacious hallway and a large family room, a modern kitchen with dining area, the laundry facilities and a toilet. The kitchen is fully equipped with an induction stove top, oven and dishwasher.
Upstairs you will find a modern bathroom with a bath, shower and double sink. There are three bedrooms upstairs, one with a double bed, one with two single beds and one with a crib for a baby up to 2,5 years.
Parking is free behind the house or in the street.

Guest access
You will have full access to the whole house and the garden, except for the top floor of the house.
